Package: farsdata
Type: Package
Title: Cleaning and Plotting of Data on Fatal Accidents in USA
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Shuvrarghya Ghosh
Maintainer: Shuvrarghya Ghosh <argha1510@gmail.com>
Description: The functions provided in this package will be using data from the US National Highway
             Traffic Safety Administration's Fatality Analysis Reporting System, which is a nationwide census
             providing the American public yearly data regarding fatal injuries suffered in motor vehicle 
             traffic crashes. The package uses datasets on accidents recorded in the years 2013, 2014 and 2015.
             The core idea here is to clean and summarize the data and plot it on US map.This package is 
             generated as a result of assessment in Coursera and in not intended for any other use.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Imports: dplyr, readr, tidyr, graphics, maps
